{"id": 237097606, "title": "Transfer Talk: Juventus' Chiesa on Bayern Munich's shortlist - ESPN", "text": "The summer transfer window is open for the Premier League and is set to open across Europe soon, and there are plenty of moves in the works and gossip swirling around. Transfer Talk brings you all the latest buzz on rumours, comings, goings and, of course, done deals! TOP STORY: Juve open to proposals for Chiesa with Bayern interested Juventus are open to offers for winger Federico Chiesa this summer, reports Fabrizio Romano. No progress has been made over talks regarding a new deal, and it is said that the 26-year-old is set to discuss his future with his representatives when he returns from the UEFA European Championship with Italy. Chiesa will enter the final year of his contract with the Bianconeri at the end of the month, after making 37 appearances across all competitions for the Serie A side last season. Bayern Munich are one of the sides keeping tabs on him, according to Sky Sports Deutschland's Florian Plettenberg, with the Bundesliga club adding him to their shortlist. It is believed that an offer between \u20ac30 million and \u20ac40m would be required to reach an agreement over a fee. Chiesa was a standout performer for Italy as they secured a 2-1 victory over Albania in their European Championship opener on Saturday. PAPER GOSSIP - Manchester United are considering a player exchange offer that would see Aaron Wan-Bissaka included as part of a deal to sign Crystal Palace centre-back Marc Gu\u00e9hi, reports Team Talk. The Red Devils are reported to see the 23-year-old as an alternative to Jarrad Branthwaite, as distance remains over a transfer fee with Everton. Palace had previously been looking for a fee in the region of \u00a350m for Guehi. - AC Milan and France international left-back Theo Hern\u00e1ndez will look to leave the San Siro if an agreement isn't reached over a new contract, reports Calciomercato. Talks are believed to have been ongoing throughout the season over an extension, with the 26-year-old seen as a key player for the Rossoneri, and it is reported that they would only consider offers in the region of \u20ac90m to part ways with him. - Barcelona are behind in the race to sign Everton defensive midfielder Amadou Onana, reports Mundo Deportivo. While the Blaugrana believe the 22-year-old is an ideal option to play in the pivot role, they aren't optimistic of being able to reach an agreement over a fee, with previous reports indicating that the Toffees would look for a minimum of \u00a350m to agree to a deal. Arsenal, Bayern Munich, and Manchester United are believed to be among the sides interested in him. - An agreement has been reached over personal terms between Aston Villa and Juventus winger Samuel Iling-Junior, reports Nicolo Schira. The Villans have been looking at a move for the 20-year-old England youth international as part of the deal that is set to see Douglas Luiz head in the other direction. Talks are also ongoing over a move to sign USMNT and Bianconeri midfielder Weston McKennie. - A move for Manchester United centre-back Victor Lindel\u00f6f is being explored by Fenerbahce, reports the Daily Mail. Manager Jose Mourinho is reported to be open to a reunion with the 29-year-old, who is available for transfer this summer as the Red Devils look to make room for squad reinforcements. The Sweden international has made 259 total appearances for the Premier League side.", "summary": "Federico Chiesa is linked with a possible move this summer. Transfer Talk is with the latest.", "url": "https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/40373174/transfer-talk-juventus-chiesa-bayern-munichs-shortlist", "image": "https://a.espncdn.com/photo/2024/0617/r1347079_1296x729_16-9.jpg", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-18 00:24:48", "author": "Adam Brown", "authors": ["Adam Brown"], "language": "en", "catgory": "sports", "source_country": "US", "sentiment": 0.156}